  <!-- ===== MTF SEBI Regulations & Compliance ===== -->
  <section class="section stack sec-tint" id="sec-sebi" data-section="sebi" style="gap:56px;justify-content:center">
    <div class="stack" style="gap:16px">
      <h2 class="sec-title">MTF SEBI Regulations &amp; Compliance</h2>
      <p class="sec-lead" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Margin Trading Facility (MTF) in India is a SEBI‑approved product, fully regulated to protect investors and ensure transparency. Brokers must strictly follow SEBI circulars and exchange guidelines when offering MTF.</p>
      <h3 class="sub-title">SEBI Guidelines for MTF</h3>
    </div>
    <ul class="bullets">
      <li>Regulatory Circulars: Governed by SEBI circular CIR/MRD/DP/54/2017 and subsequent amendments.</li>
      <li>Broker Eligibility: Only SEBI‑registered brokers with specific approval can offer MTF.</li>
      <li>Stock Eligibility: NSE/BSE define eligible securities based on liquidity and market cap.</li>
      <li>Margin Requirement: Brokers must collect minimum upfront margin as per exchange rules.</li>
      <li>Funding Source: MTF positions must be funded via broker's own capital or NBFCs — not client funds.</li>
      <li>Pledged Shares: Shares bought under MTF remain in the client's demat account, pledged as collateral.</li>
      <li>Daily MTM: Mark‑to‑market is applied daily; margin shortfalls must be rectified promptly.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

